WEBVTT

00:08.083 --> 00:10.166
[Ray] Previously
on  Ray Donovan...

00:10.166 --> 00:12.542
Yo, it's here.

00:14.125 --> 00:16.875
Wallet, cell phone
and your fucking bag.

00:16.875 --> 00:19.125
- Fuck!
- Oh!

00:19.125 --> 00:22.709
They robbed me, Pop.
My settlement money.

00:22.709 --> 00:24.500
They took it all!

00:24.500 --> 00:27.375
Cocaine, heroin, fentanyl.

00:27.375 --> 00:29.583
Nice work, Frank.

00:29.583 --> 00:31.875
Looks like you brought down
another crime boss.

00:31.875 --> 00:34.125
[Frank] We got a little problem
with Avi Rudin.

00:34.125 --> 00:35.792
I'm not killing Avi, Frank.

00:35.792 --> 00:37.667
Frank said you stole the drugs.

00:37.667 --> 00:41.125
He stole the shit
and partnered with me to sell.

00:41.125 --> 00:42.875
How much
are we talking about?

00:42.875 --> 00:45.083
A million. More, soon.

00:45.083 --> 00:47.208
- You're coming with me.
- Let's--let's talk this over.

00:47.208 --> 00:49.083
- Pop, what's going on?
- Come on, let's go!

00:49.083 --> 00:52.125
Why would your dad
want to get me sick?

00:52.125 --> 00:53.875
[Bridget] So you wouldn't get
the surgery

00:53.875 --> 00:56.000
and my mom could take
your place in the trial.

00:56.000 --> 00:58.375
Natalie James walked
off the set two days ago.

00:58.375 --> 00:59.709
I need you to find her.

00:59.709 --> 01:02.208
I'm pregnant.
It's Doug's

01:02.208 --> 01:03.041
And he told me
to get an abortion.

01:03.041 --> 01:05.542
[Doug]
You know Tom and Vicky?

01:05.542 --> 01:07.208
I thought they were supposed
to be fixing problems,

01:07.208 --> 01:08.792
not making them.

01:08.792 --> 01:11.208
He wants $2 million
and your husband's Oscar.

01:11.208 --> 01:13.208
I'll pay him the money,
but no Oscar.

01:13.208 --> 01:14.417
What's he got on you?

01:14.417 --> 01:15.208
The sun was going down,

01:15.208 --> 01:17.875
kids were in the back
of the car,

01:17.875 --> 01:19.458
I was drunk.

01:19.458 --> 01:21.041
He made it disappear.

01:21.041 --> 01:21.709
She's gonna want to see
exactly what you got.

01:21.709 --> 01:23.333
She knows what I got.

01:27.250 --> 01:29.542
You give this to Tom
with this message--

01:29.542 --> 01:31.917
Find the thing
you love the most

01:31.917 --> 01:33.375
and let it kill you.

01:35.917 --> 01:38.291
[Ray]
What's that?

01:38.291 --> 01:39.208
[Brogan]
Zoloft for depression.

01:39.208 --> 01:41.750
Neurontin
for anxiety at night.

01:41.750 --> 01:44.083
[retching]

01:44.083 --> 01:46.417
Don't fucking move.

01:49.667 --> 01:51.625
Stay back.

01:51.625 --> 01:53.458
[tires squealing]

01:53.458 --> 01:55.000
[engine revving]

01:56.417 --> 01:59.250
[horn honking]

01:59.250 --> 02:01.583
[tires squealing]

02:01.583 --> 02:04.709
♪ dramatic music ♪

02:04.709 --> 02:09.875
♪♪♪

02:52.125 --> 02:54.834
♪ upbeat big-band music ♪

02:54.834 --> 02:57.166
♪♪♪

02:57.166 --> 03:01.000
♪ Those tender kisses ♪

03:01.000 --> 03:05.083
♪ That we first shared ♪

03:05.083 --> 03:08.417
♪ Under the moonlight ♪

03:08.417 --> 03:11.166
♪ When I first dared ♪

03:11.166 --> 03:14.375
♪ To take you in my arms ♪

03:14.375 --> 03:16.959
♪ Hold you close
and say that I love you... ♪

03:16.959 --> 03:18.667
You look like Marilyn Monroe.

03:18.667 --> 03:21.333
Oh, yeah?

03:21.333 --> 03:24.542
Yeah.

03:24.542 --> 03:25.959
How about now?

03:25.959 --> 03:28.083
[chuckles]

03:31.166 --> 03:32.625
You can't keep
doing this, babe,

03:32.625 --> 03:35.500
every time we get bad news.

03:35.500 --> 03:37.000
Can't keep doing what?

03:37.000 --> 03:40.375
You know what.

03:40.375 --> 03:44.125
Where you taking me this time?

03:44.125 --> 03:45.000
Place with
the saltwater pool?

03:45.000 --> 03:47.375
Oh, for fuck's sake, Abs.

03:47.375 --> 03:51.542
- Am I right?
- So much for surprises.

03:51.542 --> 03:53.125
♪♪♪

03:53.125 --> 03:55.208
Come on.

03:55.208 --> 03:55.959
Lighten up.

03:55.959 --> 03:59.000
♪♪♪

03:59.000 --> 04:00.834
♪ And since that moment... ♪

04:00.834 --> 04:02.750
It's gonna be fun.

04:02.750 --> 04:06.000
♪ My life was yours ♪

04:06.000 --> 04:09.041
♪ And through the seasons ♪

04:09.041 --> 04:11.625
♪ Our love endures ♪

04:11.625 --> 04:16.083
♪ Though the ups and downs
of life, in and out-- ♪

04:16.083 --> 04:17.500
Yeah.

04:17.500 --> 04:20.417
Listen, do you know of any
other garages

04:20.417 --> 04:22.709
that might be closer?

04:23.750 --> 04:26.792
All right.

04:26.792 --> 04:28.375
We'll be here.

04:28.375 --> 04:29.542
[cell phone beeps]

04:33.041 --> 04:36.083
♪ light somber music ♪

04:36.083 --> 04:41.250
♪♪♪

04:44.417 --> 04:46.750
[Ray] Abs?

04:46.750 --> 04:51.625
♪♪♪

04:59.208 --> 05:04.125
♪ Right in front of Jesus ♪

05:04.125 --> 05:06.625
♪ Why would you kick me ♪

05:06.625 --> 05:09.000
♪ To the curb? ♪

05:09.000 --> 05:12.166
[truck beeping]

05:16.875 --> 05:19.667
[chains rattling]

05:19.667 --> 05:24.583
♪♪♪

05:40.917 --> 05:43.917
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

05:43.917 --> 05:46.083
[light, jazzy music playing]

05:46.083 --> 05:47.959
[girl] Don't let go.
Don't let go.

05:47.959 --> 05:53.083
♪♪♪

05:54.583 --> 05:56.250
[man] Good.
Want to go again?

05:56.250 --> 06:00.959
♪♪♪

06:10.667 --> 06:12.542
What the fuck?

06:12.542 --> 06:14.500
[chuckles]

06:14.500 --> 06:15.917
Nice. In the middle
of the desert.

06:15.917 --> 06:18.709
[Abby mutters]

06:18.709 --> 06:23.083
♪♪♪

06:23.083 --> 06:24.667
Want to skate?

06:24.667 --> 06:25.417
[man] Hey, you want
a hot chocolate?

06:25.417 --> 06:27.667
- [chuckles]
- It'll be fun.

06:30.792 --> 06:32.542
- I can't.
- What do you mean you can't?

06:32.542 --> 06:35.083
You don't remember how?

06:35.083 --> 06:36.709
No, I remember how.

06:36.709 --> 06:39.208
So?

06:39.208 --> 06:40.834
Fucking bully.

06:40.834 --> 06:42.834
Come on.

06:42.834 --> 06:45.750
[indistinct chatter]

06:59.792 --> 07:03.083
[car alarm chirps]

07:03.083 --> 07:05.333
See, a great hockey player

07:05.333 --> 07:07.750
plays off the puck, you know?

07:07.750 --> 07:09.625
Anticipates.

07:09.625 --> 07:13.583
Yeah, but, babe, you were never
a great hockey player.

07:13.583 --> 07:16.125
I didn't say I was
a great hockey player.

07:16.125 --> 07:19.250
You know, in my day,
I won a couple games.

07:19.250 --> 07:19.875
Well, what day was that?

07:19.875 --> 07:22.834
What?

07:22.834 --> 07:26.583
Oh, right. There was that one.

07:26.583 --> 07:27.417
[chuckles]

07:27.417 --> 07:30.792
Fuck you.
You're on your own.

07:34.083 --> 07:37.291
[sighs] We just gonna
leave our stuff?

07:37.291 --> 07:40.458
[grand orchestral music playing]

07:40.458 --> 07:43.375
♪♪♪

07:43.375 --> 07:44.250
I used to be able to do that!

07:44.250 --> 07:48.125
- Yeah?
- Yeah!

07:48.125 --> 07:50.291
One time around.
What's that called?

07:50.291 --> 07:52.792
[laughs] You don't know
what it's called,

07:52.792 --> 07:54.959
- but you could do it.
- Yeah!

07:54.959 --> 07:57.458
Maggie Faraday taught me
at Murphy Rink.

07:57.458 --> 07:59.166
- Yeah?
- Yeah. I swear to God,

07:59.166 --> 08:02.792
I could do that.

08:02.792 --> 08:05.291
- Do you remember Maggie?
- Sure.

08:05.291 --> 08:07.500
Two abortions in tenth grade.

08:07.500 --> 08:11.000
That's right.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.041
I wonder where she's at.

08:15.917 --> 08:19.041
A Salchow.
[laughs]

08:19.041 --> 08:22.000
[sighs happily]

08:23.166 --> 08:26.500
- You all right?
- Yeah.

08:27.083 --> 08:30.417
[man] I got this!

08:30.417 --> 08:32.000
I always wanted to wear

08:32.000 --> 08:33.750
one of those
sparkly little outfits.

08:33.750 --> 08:35.709
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

08:35.709 --> 08:38.750
I don't know.
It's not too late.

08:38.750 --> 08:39.792
[laughs]
Yeah, you wish.

08:43.750 --> 08:46.291
[Abby grunts]

08:48.333 --> 08:52.083
You all right?

08:52.083 --> 08:53.125
Come on. Let's go sit down.

08:53.125 --> 08:56.208
Let's go.

08:57.792 --> 08:59.667
What happened?

09:02.000 --> 09:04.917
[indistinct chatter]

09:04.917 --> 09:06.750
[Ray]
I'll get you some water.

09:06.750 --> 09:10.500
It's okay. [sighs]

09:13.583 --> 09:16.792
[laughter, indistinct shouting]

09:16.792 --> 09:17.834
Abs...

09:20.000 --> 09:20.834
I'm fine.

09:27.750 --> 09:33.500
You're running around
your whole life, killing people,

09:33.500 --> 09:36.875
hanging off cliffs or whatever
the fuck it is you do.

09:39.417 --> 09:42.542
You're probably gonna live
till you're 100 years old.

09:44.667 --> 09:47.333
Hardly ever done anything...

09:48.709 --> 09:50.750
Except raise your kids,

09:50.750 --> 09:53.875
look after you
and your goddamn family.

09:55.208 --> 09:56.542
[scoffs]

09:56.542 --> 09:59.333
I'm gonna be dead in my 40s.

10:00.834 --> 10:03.208
No, you're not.

10:04.500 --> 10:07.375
I want to stop treatment.

10:10.000 --> 10:12.166
We're gonna get you better,
sweetheart.

10:12.166 --> 10:14.083
I promise.

10:17.500 --> 10:19.125
I'm not getting better, Ray.

10:19.125 --> 10:22.083
Sure you are.

10:22.083 --> 10:23.583
You're just tired,
that's all.

10:23.583 --> 10:25.166
[gasps softly]

10:25.166 --> 10:27.083
I know how hard
this has been for you.

10:27.083 --> 10:30.291
No, you don't! No!

10:30.291 --> 10:33.750
You don't know.

10:37.375 --> 10:39.125
This...

10:40.959 --> 10:45.959
[voice breaking] This is
some godless fucking bullshit,

10:45.959 --> 10:48.166
is what this is.

10:50.542 --> 10:54.959
Are you fucking kidding me?

10:54.959 --> 10:58.083
Are you trying to figure out
how many hours

10:58.083 --> 11:00.667
that you have got left
to live?

11:03.291 --> 11:05.959
[crying] No.

11:05.959 --> 11:09.250
[sniffles]

11:09.250 --> 11:12.166
[indistinct shouting]

11:16.000 --> 11:19.959
It's gonna get worse
before it gets worse.

11:22.583 --> 11:24.250
Let's go home, sweetheart.

11:24.250 --> 11:26.333
Come on.

11:26.333 --> 11:29.166
I want to feel good...

11:29.166 --> 11:31.375
in my body...

11:31.375 --> 11:34.000
before I die.

11:34.000 --> 11:37.000
[sighs]

11:37.000 --> 11:40.792
[sniffles]

11:40.792 --> 11:43.208
I got to stop treatment.

11:43.208 --> 11:44.834
Come on, Abs.

11:44.834 --> 11:49.250
Take your skates off.
Let's go home.

11:49.250 --> 11:50.917
You want me to do it
for you?

11:50.917 --> 11:53.834
- Yeah.
- [smooches]

11:57.291 --> 11:58.375
[zipper opens]

11:58.375 --> 12:02.041
[sighs]

12:08.375 --> 12:10.834
Thank you.

12:25.834 --> 12:28.000
[engine rumbling]

12:37.000 --> 12:39.875
[whirring]

12:43.250 --> 12:45.291
♪ dramatic music ♪

12:45.291 --> 12:50.041
♪♪♪

13:08.000 --> 13:11.041
[indistinct chatter,
telephones ringing]

13:16.959 --> 13:19.542
[sighs]

13:19.542 --> 13:20.375
License plate
or citation number?

13:20.375 --> 13:23.625
2SAM564, please.

13:23.625 --> 13:24.500
[keys clacking]

13:24.500 --> 13:30.417
♪♪♪

13:37.125 --> 13:40.000
[lock clicks]

13:54.375 --> 13:57.125
[clerk] You can't just park
in front of a fire station.

13:58.625 --> 14:01.166
Yeah, well,
I figured that out.

14:03.667 --> 14:07.834
Gary. 17473.

14:14.709 --> 14:17.542
[car alarm chirps]

14:22.375 --> 14:23.834
[engine turning over]

14:23.834 --> 14:27.375
[tires squealing]

14:27.375 --> 14:32.542
♪♪♪

14:50.208 --> 14:52.208
[grunts]

14:56.959 --> 14:59.291
All good?

14:59.291 --> 15:00.625
Yeah.

15:00.625 --> 15:04.375
All right, what now?

15:04.375 --> 15:06.625
Find Tom Minor.

15:06.625 --> 15:09.041
All right.

15:15.083 --> 15:17.709
[door clanking closed,
buzzer sounds]

15:17.709 --> 15:20.917
[indistinct chatter]

15:28.750 --> 15:29.500
Hey, kiddo.

15:29.500 --> 15:31.417
[sighs]

15:31.417 --> 15:32.709
You all right?

15:32.709 --> 15:34.583
What the fuck
is going on, Mick?

15:34.583 --> 15:38.083
It's just a little
misunderstanding, is all.

15:38.083 --> 15:40.417
He told me--

15:40.417 --> 15:44.333
he threatened me with four
consecutive life sentences.

15:44.333 --> 15:46.041
He don't mean it.

15:46.041 --> 15:48.625
Did you know he was
gonna arrest me?

15:48.625 --> 15:52.375
No. No, I did not.

15:52.875 --> 15:55.875
He had pictures...

15:55.875 --> 15:58.709
- from Nevada.
- I know.

15:58.709 --> 15:59.709
You fucking know?

15:59.709 --> 16:03.125
I'm taking care of it.

16:03.125 --> 16:07.041
- How, Mickey?
- Don't worry about it, kiddo.

16:07.041 --> 16:08.750
Just keep your head down.

16:08.750 --> 16:10.083
I'll have you holding
your little girl

16:10.083 --> 16:11.625
by tomorrow night,
I promise you.

16:11.625 --> 16:14.333
Just keep your head down.

16:14.333 --> 16:16.417
[buzzer sounds]

16:16.417 --> 16:17.583
Fuck you, Mickey.

16:17.583 --> 16:19.542
Trust me.

16:19.542 --> 16:22.750
Fuck you!

16:22.750 --> 16:25.792
♪ ominous music ♪

16:25.792 --> 16:29.667
♪♪♪

16:29.667 --> 16:32.709
[doorbell rings]

16:37.083 --> 16:37.875
Ray.

16:37.875 --> 16:42.041
Your mother's expecting me.

16:42.041 --> 16:44.250
Mom!

16:44.250 --> 16:45.375
She'll be down
in a minute.

16:45.375 --> 16:47.000
[man on television]
Jack be nimble. Jack be quick.

16:47.000 --> 16:49.542
Jack knocked
over a candlestick

16:49.542 --> 16:51.041
onto the shag carpeting,

16:51.041 --> 16:52.250
and his pants ignited
into flame.

16:52.250 --> 16:55.291
[imitating Jack Torrance]
All work and no play

16:55.291 --> 16:59.041
makes Jack a dull boy.

16:59.041 --> 17:02.041
What?

17:02.041 --> 17:04.166
The Shining?

17:04.166 --> 17:07.792
Jack Nicholson, Shelley Duvall.

17:07.792 --> 17:10.709
Yeah, sure.

17:10.709 --> 17:15.333
I think Shelley Duvall
is the perfect woman.

17:15.333 --> 17:17.166
[smacks lips]
Those teeth.

17:17.166 --> 17:18.959
[chuckles]

17:18.959 --> 17:20.083
Yeah, Stanley Kubrick told
everyone on the movie

17:20.083 --> 17:23.166
to ignore her
and not eat lunch with her

17:23.166 --> 17:25.250
and to say terrible things
about her

17:25.250 --> 17:27.750
so it would make her feel
really lonely in the movie.

17:27.750 --> 17:31.250
And it--it worked.

17:33.583 --> 17:36.083
- Is your mom--
- Wendy.

17:36.083 --> 17:38.417
But Shelley
had such a bad time

17:38.417 --> 17:41.500
that her hair fell out.

17:41.500 --> 17:45.583
But I'd love her
even if she was bald.

17:45.583 --> 17:48.667
[Sam] Would you give us
a moment, please?

17:48.667 --> 17:51.333
Thanks, George.

17:58.500 --> 18:00.000
Everything?

18:00.000 --> 18:01.166
We should talk about my fee.

18:01.166 --> 18:03.709
I thought Doug
was taking care of you.

18:03.709 --> 18:05.250
Landry gave me
20 grand for the drop.

18:05.250 --> 18:06.917
No one said anything
about Vicky Delgatti

18:06.917 --> 18:09.750
putting a gun to my head.

18:09.750 --> 18:13.125
I see.
[inhales deeply]

18:13.125 --> 18:15.667
I'm gonna have a drink.
You want one?

18:15.667 --> 18:18.000
- Look, I didn't come here--
- Good.

18:18.000 --> 18:20.583
[sighs]

18:20.583 --> 18:23.083
- I don't like tequila.
- No, whiskey.

18:23.083 --> 18:26.291
Good Irish Catholic boy.

18:35.375 --> 18:38.417
♪ somber music ♪

18:38.417 --> 18:43.291
♪♪♪

18:49.083 --> 18:52.583
Have you been thinking
about me?

18:54.125 --> 18:56.000
What?

18:56.000 --> 18:58.792
It's a simple question.
Have you been thinking about me?

18:58.792 --> 19:02.583
♪♪♪

19:02.583 --> 19:06.041
Yeah.

19:07.041 --> 19:09.625
See, she--
she bit the button here.

19:09.625 --> 19:11.083
She--she always liked
to bite off her buttons

19:11.083 --> 19:14.417
I asked her why,
and she said it...

19:14.417 --> 19:16.208
made her happy.

19:16.208 --> 19:18.959
She was born
with a lot of little teeth,

19:18.959 --> 19:21.834
and the very first time
that I nursed her, she...

19:21.834 --> 19:25.792
she bit me.

19:25.792 --> 19:30.250
I knew at that moment that she
was the perfect little...

19:30.250 --> 19:33.500
angel beast.

19:33.500 --> 19:38.375
♪♪♪

19:45.083 --> 19:46.291
Yes, I would like you
to work for me from now on.

19:46.291 --> 19:49.542
Whatever your fee is,
I'll pay it.

19:49.542 --> 19:54.458
♪♪♪

20:23.875 --> 20:29.792
♪♪♪

20:29.792 --> 20:32.750
[dog barking in the distance]

20:44.500 --> 20:48.041
- [doorbell rings]
- Okay. You're good.

20:48.041 --> 20:51.208
[exhales deeply]
Okay.

20:52.959 --> 20:55.750
- Ahh.
- Oh, look who it is, Maria.

20:55.750 --> 20:56.709
It's Carmen.
It's your best friend.

20:56.709 --> 21:00.750
- Good morning, sweetheart.
- Oh, yeah.

21:00.750 --> 21:02.959
I, uh--
I may be a little late.

21:02.959 --> 21:04.250
We close at six, Mickey.

21:04.250 --> 21:08.500
Right. Thank you, sweetheart.

21:08.500 --> 21:10.917
Say good-bye to Grandpa.
Say good-bye to Grandpa.

21:10.917 --> 21:12.458
Hasta luego.

21:12.458 --> 21:13.500
- Bye-bye, tootsie.
- See you later.

21:13.500 --> 21:17.750
[gasps] El capitán.
Diga: "Hasta luego."

21:17.750 --> 21:21.625
Okay.

21:21.625 --> 21:25.041
[indistinct chatter,
dog barking in the distance]

21:25.041 --> 21:28.792
♪ dramatic music ♪

21:28.792 --> 21:34.000
♪♪♪

21:44.417 --> 21:47.458
[engine turning over]

21:47.458 --> 21:50.000
♪♪♪

21:50.000 --> 21:53.166
[indistinct chatter]

21:56.041 --> 21:58.291
[Punch]
Hey! Look who's here.

21:58.291 --> 22:03.125
Oh, my God. You look great.

22:03.125 --> 22:05.417
Look at that. No shaking.

22:05.417 --> 22:06.250
Oh, my God. That's incredible.

22:06.250 --> 22:09.125
It's like--and there's that.

22:09.125 --> 22:11.333
- Hi.
- Yo, what's up?

22:11.333 --> 22:15.166
- That's Amazing.
- Holy shit, you're a new man.

22:15.166 --> 22:17.041
[chuckles]

22:17.041 --> 22:18.834
- Damon.
- What's up, Punch?

22:18.834 --> 22:20.709
Hey, I just want to let you know
I really appreciate

22:20.709 --> 22:21.875
you and Hector letting me
train here and all that.

22:21.875 --> 22:25.166
